Actress Rebel Wilson announced her engagement to her partner Ramona Agruma. The 42-year-old took to Instagram to share her happy news with a picture of the pair in Disneyland. Holding Ramona’s hand to the camera, the Pitch Perfect star showed off the glittering diamond and matched her new fiancee in a stripped pink shirt. Alongside the two images that also showed Rebel down on one knee surrounded by pink petals and clutching a blue Tiffany’s box, the famous face penned a caption sharing her update. She wrote: ‘We said YES! ‘Thank you @tiffanyandco for the stunning ring 💍 and to Bob Iger and the incredible team at Disneyland @disneyweddings for pulling off this magical surprise! [sic]’. Underneath her happy news fans and friends rushed to offer their well wishes and words of congratulations. ‘OMGGG YESSS so happy for you too [sic],’ one wrote while another typed: ‘Yaaayyyy congratulations Rebel! [sic]’. A fan filled the star’s comment section with: ‘HEART IS BURSTING!! Congratulations [sic]’. Rebel first confirmed she was in a relationship with the entrepreneur in June of last year. The founder and owner of athleisure brand Lemon Ve Limon has appeared many times on the actress’s social media and has also opened up about co-parenting with Rebel following the arrival of her little girl via surrogate. This is a breaking news story, more to follow soon… Check back shortly for further updates. If you’ve got a celebrity story, video or pictures get in touch with the Metro.co.uk entertainment team by emailing us celebtips@metro.co.uk, calling 020 3615 2145 or by visiting our Submit Stuff page – we’d love to hear from you. For more stories like this, check our entertainment page. Follow Metro.co.uk Entertainment on Twitter and Facebook for the latest celeb and entertainment updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here. MORE : Rebel Wilson ‘really sad’ after first surrogate miscarried before welcoming 